from proinsulin to insulin","Processed from C-peptide to proinsulin to insulin","Processed as active insulin that requires no further modification","Processed from preproinsulin to proinsulin to insulin","Processed from proinsulin to preproinsulin to insulin"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EInsulin is \u003Cstrong\u003Eprocessed from preproinsulin to proinsulin to insulin\u003C/strong\u003E. The process begins with preproinsulin synthesis in the rough endoplasmic reticulum. The signal peptide is cleaved to form proinsulin, which moves to the Golgi apparatus where it is cleaved to produce insulin and C-peptide in equimolar amounts.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EProcessed from proinsulin to insulin\u003C/strong\u003E - This omits the initial preproinsulin stage which is essential for proper protein targeting\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EProcessed from C-peptide to proinsulin to insulin\u003C/strong\u003E - This reverses the order; C-peptide is a product of proinsulin cleavage, not a precursor\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EProcessed as active insulin that requires no further modification\u003C/strong\u003E - Insulin requires extensive processing through multiple precursor forms\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EProcessed from proinsulin to preproinsulin to insulin\u003C/strong\u003E - This reverses the correct order; preproinsulin is the initial form\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe processing of insulin is a highly regulated process that ensures the production of functional hormone. C-peptide levels can be measured to assess endogenous insulin production since they are secreted in equal amounts.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Insulin is synthesised by beta cells, where it is processed from preproinsulin to proinsulin to insulin.","Proinsulin is cleaved in the Golgi apparatus to form insulin and C-peptide in equal amounts.","C-peptide levels can be measured as a surrogate of insulin production, since they are produced in equal amounts"],"references":["Therapeutic Guidelines. Melbourne: Therapeutic Guidelines Limited. Available from: https://www.tg.org.au","Ritter J, Flower RJ (Rod J), Henderson G (Graeme), et al.\u00a0Rang and Dale\u2019s Pharmacology. Tenth edition. Elsevier; 2024.","Australian Medicines Handbook\u00a0(online). Adelaide: Australian Medicines Handbook Pty Ltd. Available from:\u00a0https://amhonline.amh.net.au/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"62030"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16896"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"62030","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/62030"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-03T17:06:37+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-03T17:07:05+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9586"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76533"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app